This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new type of network unit and develops techniques to train it effectively. It also discusses the susceptibility of standard neural network techniques to adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with the ability of neural networks to classify inputs correctly, which is a fundamental problem in AI. 

The paper also discusses the performance of the networks on image classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The topic of adversarial attacks is closely related to the field of computer security, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

Finally, the paper introduces a new type of network unit that is highly non-linear, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
